<div class="homepage-container">
    <div class="page-hero page-hero-compact">
        <div class="page-hero-bg"></div>
        <div class="page-hero-content">
            <span class="page-hero-label">About</span>
            <h1 class="page-hero-title">F1 Elo</h1>
            <p class="page-hero-meta">A continuous rating system for every F1 driver since 1950</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="elo-explanation">
        <p>
            F1 Elo is an independent project that applies the
            <strong>Elo rating system</strong>&mdash;originally designed for chess&mdash;to
            every Formula 1 race since the 1950 British Grand Prix. The goal is to provide a
            single, continuous metric that captures how drivers and constructors perform
            <em>relative to each other</em>, across eras.
        </p>
    </div>

    <%# Why Elo %>
    <div class="about-card card">
        <div class="about-card-header">
            <span class="about-card-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chart-line"></i></span>
            <h3>Why Elo?</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="about-card-body">
            <p>
                Championship points are great for ranking drivers within a single season, but they
                change format regularly and can't compare across decades. Elo ratings solve this:
                every driver starts at the same baseline, and ratings adjust after each race based
                on head-to-head pairwise comparisons against every other finisher.
            </p>
            <p>
                A race win against strong opponents earns more than a win against weaker fields,
                and vice versa. The result is a number that rises when a driver outperforms
                expectations and falls when they underperform&mdash;regardless of era, car
                advantage, or points system.
            </p>
            <div class="about-links-row">
                <%= link_to elo_path, class: "about-link" do %>
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-graduation-cap"></i> How Elo Works
                <% end %>
                <%= link_to elo_milestones_path, class: "about-link" do %>
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-trophy"></i> Elo Records
                <% end %>
                <%= link_to peak_elo_drivers_path, class: "about-link" do %>
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-mountain-sun"></i> All-Time Rankings
                <% end %>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <%# Dynamic Colors %>
    <div class="about-card card">
        <div class="about-card-header">
            <span class="about-card-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-palette"></i></span>
            <h3>Why Does the Color Change?</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="about-card-body">
            <p>
                You may notice the accent color of this site shifts as you navigate. Each page
                is tinted with the <strong>constructor color</strong> of the relevant driver or team.
            </p>
            <div class="about-color-grid">
                <div class="about-color-item">
                    <span class="about-color-dot" style="background: #e80020;"></span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Driver pages</strong>
                        <span>Color of the driver's current or most recent team</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="about-color-item">
                    <span class="about-color-dot" style="background: #ff8000;"></span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Race pages</strong>
                        <span>Tinted to the race winner's constructor</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="about-color-item">
                    <span class="about-color-dot" style="background: #27f4d2;"></span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Season pages</strong>
                        <span>The world champion's team color</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="about-color-item">
                    <span class="about-color-dot" style="background: #0600ef;"></span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Constructor pages</strong>
                        <span>That team's brand color directly</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="about-color-item">
                    <span class="about-color-dot" style="background: #e10600;"></span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Home &amp; stats</strong>
                        <span>Current world champion's color, or F1 red</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="about-muted">
                This creates a subtle sense of immersion: browsing Ferrari history feels red,
                reviewing a Mercedes-dominant era shifts to teal, and exploring classic Lotus
                seasons turns green.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <%# Modern Era %>
    <div class="about-card card">
        <div class="about-card-header">
            <span class="about-card-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-stopwatch"></i></span>
            <h3>Modern Era</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="about-card-body">
            <p>
                Since around 1996, Formula 1 has had more standardised regulations, consistent
                race formats, and richer data. Many of our
                <%= link_to "badges", badges_path %> and statistical comparisons focus on this
                &ldquo;modern era&rdquo; to keep things fair.
            </p>
            <div class="about-links-row">
                <%= link_to seasons_path(from_year: 1996, to_year: Date.current.year), class: "about-link" do %>
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-filter"></i> Modern Era Seasons
                <% end %>
                <%= link_to seasons_path(from_year: 1950, to_year: 1995), class: "about-link" do %>
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-clock-rotate-left"></i> Classic Era (1950&ndash;1995)
                <% end %>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <%# Data & Sources %>
    <div class="about-card card">
        <div class="about-card-header">
            <span class="about-card-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-database"></i></span>
            <h3>Data &amp; Sources</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="about-card-body">
            <div class="about-sources-grid">
                <div class="about-source">
                    <strong>Ergast / Jolpica</strong>
                    <span>Historical race data (1950&ndash;2024)</span>
                </div>
                <div class="about-source">
                    <strong>Jolpica API</strong>
                    <span>Current-season live sync after each race</span>
                </div>
                <div class="about-source">
                    <strong>OpenF1 API</strong>
                    <span>Driver headshot images</span>
                </div>
                <div class="about-source">
                    <strong>Local Compute</strong>
                    <span>All Elo calculations run in-app</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <%# Tech & Open Source %>
    <div class="about-card card">
        <div class="about-card-header">
            <span class="about-card-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-code"></i></span>
            <h3>Open Source</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="about-card-body">
            <p>
                Built with <strong>Rails 7</strong>, <strong>PostgreSQL</strong>, and
                <strong>Bootstrap 5</strong>. Elo ratings are computed from pairwise head-to-head
                comparisons across every race finisher. The full source code is available on GitHub.
            </p>
            <div class="about-links-row">
                <a href="https://github.com/Haumer/f1" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="about-link about-link-primary">
                    <i class="fa-brands fa-github"></i> View on GitHub
                </a>
                <a href="https://github.com/Haumer/f1/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="about-link">
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-bug"></i> Report an Issue
                </a>
                <a href="https://github.com/Haumer/f1/issues/new?labels=enhancement" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="about-link">
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-lightbulb"></i> Suggest a Feature
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <%# Quick Links %>
    <div class="about-card card">
        <div class="about-card-header">
            <span class="about-card-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-compass"></i></span>
            <h3>Explore</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="about-card-body">
            <div class="about-explore-grid">
                <%= link_to stats_path, class: "about-explore-item" do %>
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-chart-bar"></i>
                    <span>Stats Hub</span>
                <% end %>
                <%= link_to compare_drivers_path, class: "about-explore-item" do %>
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-scale-balanced"></i>
                    <span>Compare Drivers</span>
                <% end %>
                <%= link_to circuits_path, class: "about-explore-item" do %>
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-road"></i>
                    <span>All Circuits</span>
                <% end %>
                <%= link_to families_constructors_path, class: "about-explore-item" do %>
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-sitemap"></i>
                    <span>Team Lineages</span>
                <% end %>
                <%= link_to calendar_races_path, class: "about-explore-item" do %>
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-calendar"></i>
                    <span><%= Date.current.year %> Calendar</span>
                <% end %>
                <%= link_to elo_path, class: "about-explore-item" do %>
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-graduation-cap"></i>
                    <span>How Elo Works</span>
                <% end %>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
